The Kenya Defence Forces in collaboration with Aero Club East Africa on Saturday treated Kenyans to a colourful airshow at the Uhuru gardens in Nairobi. The Museum Air Show Festival led by the Kenya Air Force displayed military and civilian aerobatic capabilities, as Kenyans watched in awe. The air show comes just a few days to President Uhuru Kenyatta's last Madaraka Day which will be held at the same grounds. The Kenya Wildlife Services also showcased anti-poaching drills as they entertained Kenyans. Other participants will included; Phoenix Aviation Cessna Sovereign, Kenya Airways Embraer 190 fly-past, Farmland Aviation firefighting display and aerobatics by Mark Hensman from South Africa among others.